#Aula 2

##Commands
* CREATE DATABASE <databaseName> 
 >Creates new database
* USE <databaseName> 
 >Selects database workspace
* CREATE TABLE table_name(
	column0 datatype,
	column1 datatype,
	column2 datatype,
	...
); 
 > Selects database workspace
* SELECT column1, column2, ... FROM table_name; 
 > Returns requested column data * from a given table
* SELECT * FROM cidades; 
 > Returns all columns from a given table (* is an 'all' wildcard)
* INSERT INTO <databaseName> (column1,column2,column3...) VALUES (value1,value2,value3...)
 > Inserts into a given column* the value* respectively

##Examples
```sql
CREATE DATABASE countries
USE countries
CREATE TABLE cities(
	name varchar(100), -- Dynamic allocation with max limit
	state char(2), -- Static allocation
	country char(15),
	population varchar(100),

SELECT * FROM cities;
-- Should return an empty set
INSERT INTO cities(name,state,country,population)
VALUES("Florianopolis,"SC","Brazil",300000);
SELECT * FROM cities;
-- Should return the city value
);```



